# .gitignore — tells Git which files to NEVER track or commit
#
# WHY?
#   Some files must never go into version control:
#   • .env contains secrets (JWT key) — leaking it lets anyone forge tokens
#   • .venv is huge (hundreds of MB) and can always be recreated from requirements.txt
#   • __pycache__ is auto-generated bytecode Python creates for speed — not source code
#   • mlforge.db is a local data file — each developer/server has their own

# ── Secrets ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env

# ── Virtual environment ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.venv/

# ── Python cache ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo

# ── Database ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
storage/mlforge.db

# ── Trained ML models (will be large binary files) ────────────────────────────
storage/models/
